To align a row of divs to the right using flex in CSS, we can use the justify-content property with the value of end or end center. Here's an example:

```html
<style>
  .flex-container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: end;
    align-items: center;
  }
</style>

<div class="flex-container">
  <div>Div 1</div>
  <div>Div 2</div>
  <div>Div 3</div>
</div>
```

In this example, the row of divs will be aligned to the right using the flex property.
